RETRIEVAL_HEADER_FIELD_RULES:
TITLE:
- canonical best-fit title
- exact source title if present
- if absent, synthesise from dominant heading + doc class

DOC_ID:
- preserve official identifier if present
- else synthesise stable deterministic id

OWNER_TEAM / OWNER_ROLE / JURISDICTION / DATES:
- explicit source value > inference
- if not confidently inferable -> UNKNOWN

DOC_STATUS:
- DRAFT | ACTIVE | REVIEW | SUPERSEDED | ARCHIVED | UNKNOWN

PERMISSIONS_STATE:
- INHERITED | RESTRICTED | UNKNOWN

SOURCE_SUMMARY_RULES:
- compact machine-style lines only
- include:
  - TOPIC_DOMAIN
  - PRIMARY_INTENT
  - SECONDARY_INTENT
  - RETRIEVAL_HINT
- no prose paragraph

RECALL_BLOCK_RULES:
- recall body must match compressed screenshot-style format
- no paragraph prose inside blocks
- no bullets inside blocks
- no assistant commentary inside blocks
- syntax preference:
  - KEY = VALUE
  - SET = {A, B, C}
  - FLOW = {A -> B -> C}
  - IF cond -> action
- use inline citations where available:
  - [cite: page]
  - [cite: line-range]
- terminate with END_RECALL_V#

BLOCK_NAMING_RULES:
- format = BLOCK_XX: NAME
- XX = zero-padded integer
- NAME = uppercase_with_underscores
- one coherent concept cluster per block
- avoid vague labels like SUMMARY, NOTES, GENERAL, MISC

DEFAULT_BLOCK_ORDER:
BLOCK_01 = primary_governing_logic
BLOCK_02 = process_or_flow
BLOCK_03 = systems_roles_constants_or_supporting_cluster
BLOCK_04 = SEARCH_INDEX
BLOCK_05 = OPEN_GAPS if needed

